name: Warwick Johanson

roles_in_work.title: An Interview with Warwick N. Johanson

biography: Warwick N. Johanson joined the Royal Australian Navy at age 17 and, a year later, was aboard the HMAS Australia, working alongside 950 crew. They travelled around the east coast of Australia, looking for submarines, before they went up towards New Guinea and Kokoda to help fight up there. He is a member of Bendigo RSL and talked about his experiences in a Digital Storytelling workshop at ACMI.
